ated, mystified, and maligned figure of the orator founder.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aHistory. 4aPhilosophy. 4aPolitics and Government. 4aSocial and Political Sciences. 4aSociology and Social History. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh  aHobbes, Leviathan, Virtue, Rhetoric, Sovereignty.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048557929?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048557929zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048557929/original  a978-3-11-102374-8 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA